# SubGuard — Cursor AI Rules

# Ailoitte Velocity Pod Hackathon

# B2B SaaS Subscription Manager

Cursor MUST follow these rules when generating or editing code.

Violation of these rules will break the architecture and must NEVER occur.

---

# PROJECT OVERVIEW

SubGuard is a **B2B SaaS internal subscription manager** built for the Ailoitte Velocity Pod Hackathon.

Primary Goal:
Help companies track SaaS tools, manage subscription requests, and control spending.

Tech Stack:

* Next.js 14 (App Router)
* TypeScript (strict mode)
* Supabase (Auth + Postgres + Realtime)
* Custom CSS-in-JS (NO Tailwind)
* Playwright (E2E testing)
* Vercel (deployment)

---

# CORE PRINCIPLES

Cursor must prioritize:

1. Type Safety
2. Security
3. Deterministic E2E tests
4. Clean architecture
5. Hackathon speed with production discipline

---

# FILE STRUCTURE RULES

Pages must ONLY exist inside `/app`.

Required pages:

app/login/page.tsx
app/admin/page.tsx
app/dashboard/page.tsx

Supporting directories:

lib/supabase.ts → single Supabase client
components/ → reusable UI components
e2e/subguard.spec.ts → Playwright tests
public/logo.png → application logo

Cursor MUST NOT create additional page routes unless explicitly requested.

---

# ROUTING RULES

Root route:

/ → redirect to `/login`

After login:

admin → `/admin`
employee → `/dashboard`

Authorization redirects:

Admin page must redirect employees → `/dashboard`

Dashboard page must redirect admins → `/admin`

Unauthenticated users must ALWAYS redirect to:

/login

---

# TYPESCRIPT RULES

TypeScript strict mode is mandatory.

Cursor must follow:

• NEVER use `any`
• NEVER use `// @ts-ignore`
• NEVER disable TypeScript checking

Every data structure must have an interface.

Example:

interface Subscription {
id: string
tool_name: string
monthly_cost_cents: number
user_id: string
}

All async functions MUST include return types.

Example:

async function fetchSubscriptions(): Promise<Subscription[]>

useState must always include generics:

const [requests, setRequests] = useState<Request[]>([])

---

# DATABASE RULES

Supabase is the single source of truth.

Tables:

users
subscriptions
requests

Schema expectations:

users
id (uuid)
email
role ('admin' | 'employee')

subscriptions
id
tool_name
monthly_cost_cents
user_id

requests
id
tool_name
monthly_cost_cents
justification
status ('pending' | 'approved' | 'denied')
requested_by
denial_reason
reviewed_by
reviewed_at

Money must ALWAYS be stored as **cents (integer)**.

NEVER use floating point numbers for currency.

---

# SUPABASE RULES

Supabase client must ONLY exist in:

lib/supabase.ts

Cursor must NEVER create additional Supabase clients.

Always handle both:

const { data, error } = await supabase.from("requests").select("*")

Always use typed responses:

.returns<Request[]>()

Realtime updates must use:

supabase.channel()

Realtime channels must always be cleaned up with:

supabase.removeChannel()

---

# RLS SECURITY RULES

Row Level Security MUST always remain enabled.

Employees:

• read their own requests
• insert requests
• delete their own pending requests

Admins:

• read all requests
• approve or deny requests
• create subscriptions

RLS must NEVER be disabled.

Service role keys must NEVER appear in frontend code.

---

# AUTHENTICATION RULES

Authentication must use:

supabase.auth.getSession()

Session checks must run on:

admin dashboard
employee dashboard

Unauthorized users must redirect to `/login`.

---

# SECURITY RULES

Sensitive values must ONLY come from:

process.env

Never hardcode:

API keys
database credentials
admin credentials

.env.local must NEVER be committed.

Allowed localStorage keys:

sg-theme
sg-fail-count
sg-lockout-until
sg-seen-requests

No other localStorage keys are allowed.

---

# RATE LIMITING

Login rate limit:

5 failed attempts → lockout for 5 minutes.

Countdown must display remaining lockout time.

Attempts remaining must be displayed to the user.

---

# SESSION RULES

Admin and Employee dashboards must enforce:

Idle session timeout = 30 minutes.

On timeout:

redirect → `/login`

---

# STYLING RULES

Tailwind is strictly forbidden.

All styling must use:

CSS-in-JS via `<style>` blocks inside components.

Colors must use CSS variables.

Example:

color: var(--t1)

Never hardcode colors.

Fonts:

Inter → primary
JetBrains Mono → monospace

Border radii variables:

--r: 8px
--r2: 11px

Theme switching:

Dark mode = default.

Theme must be stored using:

localStorage.setItem("sg-theme")

Theme must be applied using:

document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-theme")

---

# UI COMPONENT RULES

All pages must include:

"use client"

Icons must be inline SVG components.

Loading state must include:

Centered spinner + "Loading..." text.

Modals must use:

position: fixed
inset: 0
z-index: 999
backdrop-filter: blur(6px)

Modals must render at the root level.

---

# ADMIN DASHBOARD FEATURES

Must include:

• Real-time updates via Supabase
• Spend analytics bar chart
• Search across tabs
• Denial reason modal
• Manual subscription creation
• Audit history
• Theme toggle
• Logout modal
• 30 minute session timeout

---

# EMPLOYEE DASHBOARD FEATURES

Must include:

• Real-time updates
• Request software modal
• Cancel pending requests
• Duplicate request prevention
• Cost warning if > $500
• Notification badge for reviewed requests
• Denial reason display
• Theme toggle
• Logout modal
• 30 minute session timeout

---

# PLAYWRIGHT TEST RULES

Test file location:

e2e/subguard.spec.ts

Base URL must come from:

process.env.PLAYWRIGHT_BASE_URL

Default fallback:

https://subguard-ailoitte.vercel.app

Credentials must ONLY come from environment variables.

Never hardcode credentials.

Before each test, clear localStorage keys:

sg-fail-count
sg-lockout-until
sg-seen-requests

Required E2E flows:

1. Admin login → sees total monthly spend ≥ 0
2. Employee login → submits $50/month request
3. Admin approves request → total spend increases by exactly $50

Database must be reset before tests.

---

# TEST SELECTORS

UI must include data-test attributes:

login-email
login-password
login-submit
login-error

total-spend
pending-request-row
approve-btn
deny-btn

logout-btn

request-software-btn
subscription-card
request-row

request-modal
request-tool-name
request-monthly-cost
request-justification
request-submit-btn

---

# GIT RULES

Primary repository:

https://github.com/ERSWARAJ/SubGuard-B2B-SaaS-Subscription-Manager

Primary branch:

main

Never commit:

.env.local
node_modules
.next

Always include:

.env.example

Commit message format:

feat: new feature
fix: bug fix
ux: UI improvement
config: configuration change
chore: maintenance

---

# PERFORMANCE RULES

Cursor must prefer server-side data fetching when possible.

Avoid unnecessary client re-renders.

Realtime subscriptions must unsubscribe on component unmount.

---

# ERROR HANDLING

All Supabase operations must check for errors.

Example:

if (error) {
console.error(error)
}

User-friendly messages must be displayed.

Console logs must never expose secrets.

---

# FINAL RULE

Cursor must NEVER break these rules when generating code.

If a requested change conflicts with these rules, Cursor must:

1. Explain the conflict
2. Propose a safe alternative
